Rating: 4
This was an amazing cake - both in presentation and taste. Based on the advice from the reviewers I combined several changes to make the icing firmer and cake moist. 1) used 3 eggs and added more OJ to cake batter; 2)baked for 23 min; 3)used ultra-pasteurized whipping cream but added 1 tsp instant vanilla pudding powder per cup of cream; 4)added 1 packet of unflavored gelatin (evenly spread over 3TBS COLD water in small saucepan, let stand 1min to sotften, then boil over low-med heat stirring until dissolved, remove from heat and immediately start beating whipping cream for 2-3min, then add powdered sugar, followed by slow stream of dissolved gelatin); 5)used 1c of powdered sugar in Creme Fraiche recipe. After the modification, the frosting did not weep, cake remained moist till the next day when stored overnight even without any cover. And it is really delicious and light.

