Rating: 3
I just made this cake for Mother's Day and it received rave reviews from my family. I took the liberty of changing a few things, however. I baked the cake as the recipe described and it turned out very well. Instead of the jam and creme fraiche filling I made Berenbaum's Strawberry Cloud Cream and sliced strawberries very thinly on top of each layer of the cream. I also used a vanilla/grand marnier buttercream to frost the cake because i thought it might be a bit more stable. To readers who have had some trouble keeping fillings in the cake, I can offer a suggestion for making your cake building more enjoyable: first of all use a springform pan that is the same size as the cake. Line it with plastic wrap first with enough overhang to cover it all up when you've finished. put in one layer of cake, then pipe a line of buttercream around the edge of it. Then pipe another on top of that. It forms an edge that will help you with your filling. The filling will stay inside the cake. Just don't put too thick of a line of buttercream. I also brushed a bit of simple syrup flavored w ith grand marnier on each layer before filling to keep it moist. After put the top layer on i just wrapped it all up and refrigerated it awhile before finishing the cake. Yummy cake! The basketweave is simpler than it sounds, just go for it and have fun!

