WARNING..Ok, for those of you who can only get ultra-pasteurized cream, listen up. Your frosting is doomed. It will fall, your layers will slide, and your cake will be a mess. It will taste good, but it will be a MESS. If you suffer like I do and only have ultra-P cream available, here's what you do.....you either stablize it with unflavored gelatine, or with 1 1/2 cups of vegetable shortning. Trust me, you need the extra stability. I made the frosting the recipe calls for on Friday night. By Sat. morning, the frosting had become a pool of mush. If I had frosted the cake, it would have been a disaster. OH, and don't forget about the Grand Mariner. Don't use strawberry preserves...yuck. Use your imagination. MY cake ruled the world. Your cake, if you follow the recipe, is average at best. Feel free to write me for advice!!

