Rating: 3
I made this for Easter dinner and it was delicious. Relatively easy to make, but the frosting was not as firm as I would have liked which made it a little bit difficult to do the basket weave, but it still came out beautifully!

Rating: 1
The cake was very dense and dry, a little to sweet also. A moist and light cake would have complimented the strawberries and cream nicely, or even a classic pound cake if you favor a more dense cake. The whipped cream icing was not thick enough to use for basket weaving. My suggestion if making this cake: Drizzle each cake layer with strawberry sauce to add moistness, and top with whipped topping just before serving, forget the basket weave!

Rating: 4
I made this cake for Easter dinner and it was a tremendous success. Try using three 8 inch layers. I didn't have time to do the basket weave and no one cared it was so beautiful already.

Rating: 0
Regarding whipped cream, try to find pasturized not ultrapasturized cream. The ultrapasturization process cooks the cream to a high heat and destroys it's wonderful whipping qualities. Most ultrapasturized cream collapses after a few minutes. Keep your cream, beaters and bowl cold before whipping

Rating: 4
My husband, a pie enthusiast, said this was the best cake he had ever eaten.I took that as a positive. I have trouble whipping cream with a hand blender. My frosting was not as "firm" as it should have been, I think. Aside from perhaps using my kitchen-aid, does anyone have tips on how to perfect "whipping" cream?

Rating: 3
The recipe was well written and the instructions for icing easy to follow. Some hints based on my experience. I found that I needed to use less creme fraiche than recommended in each pastry bag to do a proper job. Also, it would be nice if the next time, the sizes of the tips could be added. You need a medium to large sized basket weave tip to make the weave look similar to the photographs.

Rating: 4
Gorgeous cake, simple to make and tastes great. No overly pretentious ingredients or techniques here. A simple but favourful cake that allows you to enjoy the strawberries and whipped cream topping.

Rating: 4
this was outstanding! I made it for Easter and it was a real hit: I'll be making it again for Mother's Day! just a couple of suggestions: chill the whipped cream icing before putting it in the pastry bags, use a well-chilled metal bowl to whip the cream. I also brushed the bottom layer of the cake with Bourbon (could use Grand Marnier or Brandy) before adding the strawberry filling- it kept the cake moister. And trust me, the basketweave design is easier than it looks, you just get the hang of it!